The paper proposes a deep learning model for population estimation from satellite imagery, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks for prediction also falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the validation of the model, which involves comparing the model's estimates to US Census data, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper addresses the use of machine learning for social problems, which falls under the social and information sciences (cs.SI) sub-category.
